      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@MuhammadRiyaz It depends on your OS and whether you&#39;re using a 32-bit or 64-bit JVM.  If you&#39;re on a 64 bit JVM, you can safely set it to anything smaller than your RAM size minus overhead for OS/other applications.  On a 32 bit VM, you&#39;ll want to keep it smaller than about 1500M (on Linux) or 1100M (on Windows) because the VM needs to allocate contiguous address space, and that&#39;s a very limited resource for 32-bit apps."
